{"id":87656,"title":"An indirect reduction technique for percutaneous fixation of calcaneus fractures.","abstract":"We describe a positioning and indirect reduction method that allows for earlier fixation of some displaced calcaneus fractures. Minimally invasive surgery with this technique can provide good results in high-risk patients while minimizing soft-tissue complications. ","date":"2014-07-22","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25046187","annotations":[{"name":"Invasiveness of surgical procedures","weight":0.6839,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Invasiveness_of_surgical_procedures"},{"name":"Redox","weight":0.22798,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Redox"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.225149,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Calcaneus","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calcaneus"},{"name":"Percutaneous","weight":0.0229389,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Percutaneous"},{"name":"Fixation (psychology)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fixation_(psychology)"},{"name":"Displacement (ship)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Displacement_(ship)"},{"name":"Indirect injection","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indirect_injection"}]}
